  "text": "The border rank R(w) of w ∈ W is defined as the smallest r ∈ N such that w can be obtained as the limit of a sequence w k ∈ W with R(w k ) ≤ r for all k. Clearly, R(w) ≤ R(w). Border rank is a natural mathematical notion closely related to the rank and it has played an important role in the discovery of fast algorithms for matrix multiplication, see [CITATION_1] . We note that the best known lower bound on the border rank of matrix multiplication [CITATION_2] states that R( n, n, n ) ≥",
